To be able to run GreenBusiness app, please follow the following steps:
1. Pull all data from Github using the following link: https://github.com/taingocbui/DBProject.git
2. Install NodeJS in your machine. Please follow the following link to install NodeJS using package manager: https://nodejs.org/en/download/package-manager/ 
3. In terminal, install the following dependencies in NodeJS using Terminal: npm install --save <dependency_names>
    body-parser
    ejs
    express
    mysql
    nodemon
    
4. In the working directory, where all files are pulled from Github, type in Terminal
    node app
5. Open a browser, direct to http://localhost:3000/
6. The app should be running with search page displayed in http://localhost:3000/

To be able to view database using workbench, please follow the following steps:
1. Open workbench
2. Select Setup New Connection
3. In field Hostname, type greenbusiness.ctoj3jsxqwtc.us-west-1.rds.amazonaws.com
4. In field Port, type 3306
5. In Username, type root
6. In Password, type password
7. Select OK

If you have any question, please feel free to email taingocbui@gmail.com. Mahalo
